An armed police officer was yesterday stabbed and injured by a suspect he had arrested in Wundanyi town.  The man was being arrested for allegedly threatening to kill his uncle.  According to the police, the injured officer was stabbed in the thigh and was taken to the Wundanyi Health Centre.  “The armed police officers had confronted the suspect in the town as he wielded a knife before he attacked one of them. The suspect fled the scene and is being sought,” said an officer.  “The police officer exercised a lot of restraint not to shoot the suspect. We are tracking him down,” added another officer.  70-year-old stabs wife to death in Sh6,000 dispute  Police seeking woman who killed another after they clashed in man’s house  Businessman stabbed to death while closing his shop  Form Four student stabbed to death in nightclub row over woman Taita Sub County Police Commander Onesmus Kombe could not confirm or deny the attack. “I have not been briefed about the attack,” he responded.  The incident comes days after a man was shot dead for allegedly attacking three police officers in Mpizinyi village, Mwatate Sub-County.  County Police Commander Patrick Okeri said police recovered crude weapons from the suspect.      Bodaboda rider detained over the brutal stabbing of two teenagers that left one of them dead  Afueni kwa wakazi wa eneo la Landi, Taita Taveta, baada ya mradi wa taa za usiku kuzinduliwa  Two air force officers escaped death narrowly after their plane crashed By Joackim Bwana | 7 hours ago By Hassan Barisa | 7 hours ago By Ishaq Jumbe | 12 hours ago By Peterson Githaiga | 1 day ago